# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
If we take a = 0, b = 1, c = 2, then the string must follow the pattern 012 012...
So we can iterate over the characters and check if `(previous + 1) % 3 = current`

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int addMinimum(String word) {
        int ans = 0;
        int prev = 2;
        int i = 0;
        while (i < word.length()) {
            int curr = word.charAt(i) - 'a';
            if ((prev+1)%3 == curr) {
                i++;
                prev = curr;
            }
            else {
                ans++;
                prev = (prev+1)%3;
            }
        }
        return ans + 2 - prev;
    }
}
```

