# Approach
1. First store the count of abc, ab, bc, ac ,a,b,c patterns in the map.
2. And then count the remaining letters from the patterns to make  string "abc".
3. Then return the no. of count.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n) 
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n) 
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int addMinimum(string s) {
        unordered_map<string,int>mp;
        for(int i=0;i<s.size();i++){
            string t="";
            int ind=s[i]-'a';
            t=t+s[i];
            int index=i;
            for(int j=i+1;j<index+3 && j<s.size();j++){

                // handle 'a' and then 'c' patterns
                  if(s[i]=='a'&&s[j]-'a'==ind+2){
                    t=t+s[j];
                    i++;
                    break;
                }

                //handle "a","b","c","ab","bc" and "abc" kind of patterns
                if(s[j]-'a'==ind+1){
                    t=t+s[j];
                    ind++;
                    i++;
                }else break;
            }
            mp[t]++;
        }
        int ans=0;
        // And then count remaining letters of different patterns to make "abc" string
        for(auto it:mp){
            if(it.first.size()==3)continue;
            else if(it.first.size()==2)ans=ans+it.second;
            else ans=ans+(it.second*2);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

