# Intuition
For any given letter at any index we need to make it like "abc". 

# Approach
We have a given pattern. For a given character we will keep on appending to the left based on patternIndex. At last we will add characters to the right so that pattern "abc" can be form 

For eg: Word -> "aaa" Pattern -> "abc";
at 0th index of word character is 'a'
at 0th index of Pattern character is 'a'
so nothing will appended to the left. 

at 1st index of word character is 'a'
at 0th index of Pattern character is 'b'
Characters are not matching so move the patternIndex in ciruclar fashion so that it matches. 
2 characters will be added before 1st Index of word 'b', 'c' and now bothe word and pattern index are pointing to the same character.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int addMinimum(String word) {
        String pattern = "abc";
        int patternIndex = 0;
        int additionalCount = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < word.length(); i++) {
            char currentChar = word.charAt(i);

            while (currentChar != pattern.charAt(patternIndex)) {
                additionalCount++;
                patternIndex = (patternIndex + 1) % 3; // loop within bounds of 'abc'
            }
            patternIndex = (patternIndex + 1) % 3; // move to next expected character in pattern
        }

        switch (word.charAt(word.length() - 1)) {
            case 'a':
                additionalCount += 2;
                break;
            case 'b':
                additionalCount += 1;
                break;
        }

        return additionalCount;
    }
}

```

