# Intuition
We need to repeat a pattern of "abc" in a given string by adding charecters .
As we can only add charecters , to add the minimum number of them we will have to use those who partialy or completely fit the pattern and expand upon them .

# Approach
In the given solution we repeat a patten of 0 , 1 , 2 in the variable pattern
```
    int pattern = 0;
    .
    .
    .
    pattern = (pattern+1)%3;
```
 and in turn repeating the pattern 'a' , 'b' , 'c' in
```
    pattern+'a'
```
We then iterate through the given string and check if the charecter at a give index matches or not .

- If the pattern and charecter at index mathch then both move forword and there is no need to add extra charecters (no change in res)
- Otherwise we need to add new charecter (res ++) and pattern moves forword


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int addMinimum(String word) {
        int res = 0 ;
        int index = 0;
        int pattern = 0;
        int len = word.length();
        while (index<len){
            if(word.charAt(index)==pattern+'a'){
                index++;
            }
            else{
                res++;
            }
            pattern = (pattern+1)%3;
        }
        return res + ('c'- word.charAt(len-1));
    }
}
```

