# Intuition &  Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

##### •	Initialize an array answer of size n, where n is the length of the input array.
##### •	Initialize two arrays prefix and suffix of size n.
##### •	Initialize two hash sets prefixset and suffixSet.
##### •	Iterate over the input array nums from left to right, and for each element nums[i], do the following:
##### • a. If  prefixset does not contain nums[i], add nums[i] to prefixset and set prefix[i] to the size of prefixset.
##### • b. If prefixset contains nums[i], set prefix[i] to the value of prefix[i-1].
##### •	Iterate over the input arrayfrom right to left, and for each element, do the following:
##### • a. If  suffixSet does not contain nums[i], add nums[i] to suffixSet and set suffix[i] to the size of suffixSet.
##### • b. If suffixSet contains nums[i], set suffix[i] to the value of suffix[i+1].
##### •	Iterate over the input array nums from left to right, and for each element, set answer[i] to prefix[i]-surffix[i+1]
##### •	Set answer[n-1] = prefix[n-1].
##### •	Return the answer array.



# Code
```java []
public int[] distinctDifferenceArray(int[] nums) {
    int n = nums.length;
    int[] answer = new int[n];
    int[] prefix = new int[n];
    int[] suffix = new int[n];
    HashSet<Integer> prefixSet = new HashSet<>();
    HashSet<Integer> suffixSet = new HashSet<>();

    // Step 1: Iterate over the input array from left to right to fill the prefix array
    for (int i = 0, j = 1; i < n; i++) {
        if (!prefixSet.contains(nums[i])) {
            prefixSet.add(nums[i]);
            prefix[i] = j++;
        } else if (i > 0) {
            prefix[i] = prefix[i-1];
        }
    }

    // Step 2: Iterate over the input array from right to left to fill the suffix array
    for (int i = n-1, j = 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        if (!suffixSet.contains(nums[i])) {
            suffixSet.add(nums[i]);
            suffix[i] = j++;
        } else if (i > 0) {
            suffix[i] = suffix[i+1];
        }
    }

    // Step 3: Iterate over the input array to fill the answer array
    for (int i = 0; i < n-1; i++) {
        answer[i] = prefix[i] - suffix[i+1];
    }
    answer[n-1] = prefix[n-1];

    return answer;
}
```
```c++ []
vector<int> distinctDifferenceArray(std::vector<int>& nums) {
    int n = nums.size();
    std::vector<int> answer(n);
    std::vector<int> prefix(n);
    std::vector<int> suffix(n);
    std::unordered_set<int> prefixSet;
    std::unordered_set<int> suffixSet;
    for (int i = 0, j = 1; i < n; i++) {
        if (prefixSet.find(nums[i]) == prefixSet.end()) {
            prefixSet.insert(nums[i]);
            prefix[i] = j++;
        } else if (i > 0) {
            prefix[i] = prefix[i-1];
        }
    }
    for (int i = n-1, j = 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        if (suffixSet.find(nums[i]) == suffixSet.end()) {
            suffixSet.insert(nums[i]);
            suffix[i] = j++;
        } else if (i < n-1) {
            suffix[i] = suffix[i+1];
        }
    }
    for (int i = 0; i < n-1; i++) {
        answer[i] = prefix[i] - suffix[i+1];
    }
    answer[n-1] = prefix[n-1];
    return answer;
}
