## **INTUTION:**
* Just calculate prefix OR (at each index prefix OR will contain OR of all its previous element) and suffix OR ( at each index suffix OR will contain OR of all its next elements.)

* Now if you are lets say standing at current position then you have to find maximum OR value of taking
OR of each value but after apply operation (multiply by 2 k times) then you have OR value of all elements
just before of this current index is in prefix array and OR value of all element next to this index in suffix array.

* So just check current number by multiplying by 2k times that whether it is generating maximum answer.

#### **Let's take the test case: [12,9] and k=1**
   Prefix is: 0 12 13 
   Suffix is: 13 9 0 
   P= 2  (P=2*K)

   On calculating --> 

**for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        res = max(res, pre[i] | (nums[i] * p) | suf[i + 1]); 
		// res=max(res,(OR of all numbers before this index) * (current num multiplied with 2k times) * OR of all number after this index) //
    }**

  res= 0 If current num is multiped by 2 k times then answer will be= 25
  res= 25 If current num is multiped by 2 k times then answer will be= 30

####  **Let's take the test case: [8,1,2] and k=2**
  Prefix is: 0 8 9 11 
 Suffix is: 11 3 2 0 
 P= 4  (P=2*k)

   On calculating --> 

**for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        res = max(res, pre[i] | (nums[i] * p) | suf[i + 1]);
    }**
 res= 0 If current num is multiped by 2 k times then answer will be= 35
 res= 35 If current num is multiped by 2 k times then answer will be= 14
 res= 35 If current num is multiped by 2 k times then answer will be= 9

so take maximum res value as answer.

**NOTE📝:**  Some people are confused that whe multiply only current number with 2k times. It may be possible that we can get max answer by spreading multiply of 2 means you can multiply by 2 with multiple numbers why only to just one number.

 Dear your doubt is genuine but let you think that when we get maximum OR value

* OR value is directly proportional to the  greater we have a number. 

* Now suppose nums=[8,1,2] and k=2 if you think that instead of multiplying by 2k times you can multiply other numbers also means multiply one 2 by 8 another 2 by other number from 1 and 2 but you are wrong here you have to think critically here that I am raising each number to its maximum value by multiplying by 2k times and i am doing it for each number so the number which is generating maximum OR will be our final answer.

* Actually 2k is also a number and we can maximise OR value if this 2k value is making a number maximum in our array.


```
long long maximumOr(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
    int n = nums.size();
    vector<long long> pre(n + 1, 0); // Stores prefix bitwise OR values
    vector<long long> suf(n + 1, 0); // Stores suffix bitwise OR values
    pre[0] = 0;
    suf[n] = 0;
    long long res = 0;
    long long p = 1; // Used to calculate the power of 2, equivalent to x^k
    p = p << k; // Left shift k positions to calculate 2^k

    // Calculate prefix bitwise OR values
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
