Make an array counting how many times each bit is in a number.
Then simply loop through each number n and compute what would happen if we doubled it k times. 
For each bit i to count, either 
(1) B[i]>1 (will count for sure no matter what is done to n)
(2) B[i]=1 and (1<<i)&n=0 (changing n won't change B[i])
(3) B[i]=0 but (n<<k)&(1<<i), doubling n k times will make it count.
Since n goes up to 10^9 which is less than 2^30, and k<=15, we go up to 45. 
```
    def maximumOr(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:
        B = [0 for _ in range(45)]

        for n in nums:
            for i in range(30):
