**First**
To obtain the maximum possible value — we should apply all the k operations on a single number `x << k`, because if we share `k` between elements the total shift will be smaller

```
         k=2      k=2
       share   single
——— ———————— ————————
101     1010    10100
 10      100       10
```
**Second**
From left to right we calculate prefix OR's.
From right to left we calculate suffix OR's.

**Third**
To perform OR for all elements `<= 1e9` and one element `> 1e9` we should split the lement to the sum
```
nums[0] = 999997022 base 10
nums[0] * 2 ** 14 = 16383951208448 base 10
                  = 11101110011010101111100101111000000000000000 base 2
nums[0] * 2 ** 14 % (1 << 30)   = 101111100101111000000000000000 base 2
nums[0] * 2 ** 14 -                   
nums[0] * 2 ** 14 % (1 << 30)
                  = 11101110011010000000000000000000000000000000 base 2
```

# Code
```
var maximumOr = function(nums, k) {
  const n = nums.length;

  const pre = new Array(n);
  pre[0] = nums[0];
  pre[-1] = 0;
  for (let i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    pre[i] = nums[i] | pre[i-1];
  }

  const suf = new Array(n+1);
  suf[n-1] = nums[n-1];
  suf[n] = 0;
  for (let i = n-2; i > 0; i--) {
    suf[i] = nums[i] | suf[i+1];
  }

  let max = -Infinity;
  const f = 2 ** k;
  const mod = 1 << 30;
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    const x = nums[i] * f;
    const rest = x % mod;
    max = Math.max(
      max,
      (x - rest) + (pre[i-1] | suf[i+1] | rest)
    )
  }

  return max
};
```

# Complexity
Time complexity: O(n) since we simply iterate on nums 3 times
Space complexity: O(n) we store prefix ans suffix values

