# Intuition
This question asks for the max OR result. The answer is ways moving the number with biggest bit for the max k times. No need to consider <k moves. And no need to move multiple numbers. Only move one single number.
Which one single number to move? Just try them all.

# Code
```
class Solution:
    def maximumOr(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:
        counter = [0]*32
        for v in nums:
            for i in range(32):
                counter[i]+=(v>>i) & 1
        res = 0
        for v in nums:
            cur = v<<k
            for i in range(32):
                cnt = counter[i]-((v>>i) & 1)
                cur |= (cnt>0)<<i
            res = max(res,cur)
        return res
```

