# Intuition
We have to left shift the elements with most significant bits 
if we shift single element k times then the most significant bit will left shift by k bits.


<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
lets say we have elements below and k is 3
8 12 15 3
1000
1100
1111
0011

Way to solve is shift the 3 elements (8, 12, 15) 
If we choose single element then most significant bit will be 4th + k ( k = 3)

We cant say which one of this will give the correct ans
  `   prefix[i] - ORs of elements 0,1,2 ... i,`
        `    suffix[i]  - ORs of elements i,i+1...n-1; `

for all nums with most significant bit present, do
   ` (nums[i] *  pow(2, k)) | pref[i-1] | suf[i+1] `

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:

    int pow(int a, int b)
    {
        if(b==0)
            return 1;
        int x = pow(a,b/2);

        if(b%2)
            return x*x*a;
        return x*x;
    }

    long long maximumOr(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        long long ans = 0 , cur = 0;
        int n = nums.size(), p = pow(2,k);
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());

        int maxBits = ceil( log2(nums[n-1] + 1.0));
        //cout << maxBits << endl;
        vector<int> pref(n), suf(n);

        pref[0] = nums[0]; suf[n-1] = nums[n-1]; 
        for(int i=1; i<n; i++)
             pref[i] = pref[i-1] | nums[i];

        for(int i=n-2; i>=0; i--)
            suf[i] = suf[i+1] | nums[i];

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++)
        {
            int bits = ceil( log2(nums[i] + 1.0));
            cur = 0;
            if(bits == maxBits)
            {     
                if(i)
                    cur =  pref[i-1];
                if(i != n-1)
                    cur = cur | suf[i+1];
                cur = cur | (long long)nums[i] * p;
                ans = max(ans, cur);
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

