# Intuition & Approach
The idea is to calculate the OR of all the values from `nums` in `total` and bits that are repeated more than once in `reps`. Then in each iteration over `nums`, we can calculate the OR for the array with 1 number edit. If the bit is set in `reps` then it should persist otherwise should be unset.


# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n * m)$$

- Space complexity: $$O(m)$$

- Where:
$$n$$ is length of the array,
$$m$$ is maximum size required to store all the bits, i.e. 64


# Code
```
long long maximumOr(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
    long long res = numeric_limits<long long>::min();
    bitset<numeric_limits<long long>::digits> total, reps;
    for (int n : nums) {
        bitset<numeric_limits<int>::digits> bits(n);
        for (size_t i = 0; i < bits.size(); ++i) {
            if (bits[i] && total[i] && !reps[i]) reps[i] = true;
            if (bits[i] && !total[i]) total[i] = true;
        }
    }
    for (int n : nums) {
        bitset<numeric_limits<long long>::digits> n_bits(n);
        bitset<numeric_limits<long long>::digits> cur(total);
        for (size_t i = 0; i < n_bits.size(); ++i)
            if (n_bits[i] && !reps[i]) cur[i] = false;
        n_bits <<= k;
        cur |= n_bits;
        res = max(res, (long long)cur.to_ullong());
    }
    return res;
}
```

