# Bruteforce Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
**Traverse all the nums and multiple every element k times and check for the maximum(ans). For this, consider prefix and suffix arrays which avoid recomputing OR for entire nums.
For example,
nums = [8,1,2], k = 2
prefix = [8,9,11]
suffix = [11,3,2]
i=0 : val = nums[0] multiple k times i.e,32
res = prefix[. . i] | val | suffix[i . .]
res at i=0: 32|suffix[1] i.e, OR of entire nums after updating nums[i] k times
Similarly for i=1: res = prefix[0] |val| suffix[2]
Similarly for i=2: res = prefix[1] | val
Answer = max(res)**

- **Time complexity: O(n*k)**
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
# Code
