# Intuition
Just build two ints - one with all numbers OR'ed, another only with those bits set which are found at least in two input numbers. Then, for every number we can unset it's bits from `or` and add all bits set in `dbl_or` (only bits in 2+ number from input) to quickly get result or OR'ing of all the other number.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(1) additional space

# Code
```
// pub struct Solution;

impl Solution {
    pub fn maximum_or(nums: Vec<i32>, k: i32) -> i64 {
        let mut or = 0;
        let mut dbl_or = 0;

        for num in &nums {
            dbl_or |= (*num & or);
            or |= *num;
        }

        let mut best = 0;
        for num in nums {
            best = best.max(
                (or & !num | dbl_or) as i64 
                    | ((num as i64) << k as usize)
            );
        }

        best
    }
}

```

