# Approach

To solve the problem, we follow these steps:

1. Convert the input string `s` into a character array `arr` for easy manipulation.
2. Determine the length of the array and store it in the variable `n`.
3. Iterate over the array from the beginning (`i = 0`) to the middle (`i < n / 2`).
4. Check if the characters at positions `i` and `j` (where `j = n - 1 - i`) are different.
5. If the characters are different, replace both characters with the lexicographically smaller one.
6. Finally, convert the modified character array `arr` back into a string and return it as the result.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public String makeSmallestPalindrome(String s) {
        char[] arr = s.toCharArray();
        int n = arr.length;
        for(int i = 0, j = n - 1; i < n / 2; i++, j--)
            if(arr[i] != arr[j]){
                char smallOne = (char) Math.min(arr[i], arr[j]);
                arr[i] = arr[j] = smallOne;
            }
        return new String(arr);
    }
}
