# Approach
I use 2 pointers, the first one start from the left, the second one start from the right.
Then I compare the value of these indexes
If the value on the left is bigger than the value on the right, update its value with the value from the right
If the value on the right is bigger than the value on the left, update its value with the value from the left
Then I increase the value of the left index, and also decrease the value of the right index to continue checking the value.
The loop will end when left index is not less then the right index anymore.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(N)

# Code
```
/**
 * @param {string} s
 * @return {string}
 */
var makeSmallestPalindrome = function(s) {
    let str = s.split('')
    let left = 0
    let right = str.length - 1
    while (left < right) {
        if (str[left] > str[right]) {
            str[left] = str[right]
        }
        else if (s[right] > s[left]) {
            str[right] = str[left]
        }
        left++
        right--
    }
    return str.join('')
};
```

