# Code
```
class Solution {
    public String makeSmallestPalindrome(String s) {
        int i = 0;
        int j = s.length() - 1;
        Character[] arr = new Character[j + 1];

        while (i <= j) {
            char si = s.charAt(i);
            char ej = s.charAt(j);

            if (si != ej) {
                // To make the palindrome smallest, we need to replace the larger character
                // with the smaller one, so the difference in their ASCII values should be minimized.
                if (si > ej) {
                    arr[i] = s.charAt(j);
                    arr[j] = s.charAt(j);
                } else {
                    arr[i] = s.charAt(i);
                    arr[j] = s.charAt(i);
                }
            } else {
                arr[i] = s.charAt(i);
                arr[j] = s.charAt(j);
            }
            i++;
            j--;
        }

        // Convert the Character array to a String
        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();
        for (char c : arr) {
                result.append(c);
            }
        return result.toString();
    }
}

```

