# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We have to break or partition the string such that maximum partitions are present in dictionary. The summation of length of partitions not present in dictionary will be our result.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
dp[i] denotes how many extra characters are left when we consider the substring [0, i].

At each index i, we will try to partition at all previous indices and check if partition [j + 1, i] is present in dictionary or not.

# Case - 1 : Partition [j + 1, i] is present in dictionary

Since, our current partition is present in dictionary, our result will be that of the previous partitions.

Example : For "leetscode", let us assume we create a partition at index 4.
Our two partitions will be
# leets | code
Since, "code" is present in string our result will be the number of extra characters in "leets", i.e, 1.



# Case - 2 : Partition [j + 1, i] is not present in dictionary

Since, our current partition is not present in dictionary, our complete partition will constitute the extra characters in result.
Hence, our result will be that of the previous partitions + length of current partition.

Example : For "leetscod", let us assume we create a partition at index 4.
Our two partitions will be
# leets | cod
Since, "cod" is present in string our result will be the number of extra characters in "leets", i.e, 1 and length of current partition, i.e, 3
Hence, our result will be 1 + 3 = 4;

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n^2)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int minExtraChar(String s, String[] dictionary) {

        int n = s.length();

        Set<String> dict = new HashSet<>();

        for (String word : dictionary) {
            dict.add(word);
        }

        int[] dp = new int[n];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

            dp[i] = dict.contains(s.substring(0, i + 1)) ? 0 : i + 1;

            for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {

                String partition = s.substring(j + 1, i + 1);

                if (dict.contains(partition)) {
                    dp[i] = Math.min(dp[i], dp[j]);
                } else {
                    dp[i] = Math.min(dp[i], dp[j] + i - j); // i - j = partition.length()
                }
            }
        }

        return dp[n - 1];
    }
}
```

