``` java []
class Solution {
    int n;
    public boolean wordBreak(String s, List<String> wordDict) {
        n = s.length();
        Boolean[] memo = new Boolean[n];
        return wordBreak(0, s, new HashSet<>(wordDict), memo);
    }
    boolean wordBreak(int idx, String s, Set<String> dict, Boolean[] memo) {
        if(idx == n) {
            return true;
        }
        if(memo[idx]!=null) {
            return memo[idx];
        }
        // read i as end and idx as start, it will be easy to understand
        for(int i=idx+1; i<=n; i++) {
            if(dict.contains(s.substring(idx, i))&&wordBreak(i, s, dict, memo)) {
                return memo[idx] = true;
            }
        }
        return memo[idx] = false;
    }
}
```

# HashSet + Recursion: (TLE)

**Can we implement in similar fashion? Instead of keeping true or false, we should keep the penalty or unmatched words.**

``` java []
class Solution {
    int n;
    public int minExtraChar(String s, String[] dictionary) {
        n = s.length();
        Set<String> dict = new HashSet<>(Arrays.asList(dictionary));
        return recurse(0, s, dict);
    }
    int recurse(int start, String s, Set<String> dict) {
        if(start == n) {
            return 0;
        }

        int localMin = Integer.MAX_VALUE;

        for(int end=start+1; end<=n; end++) {
            // in c++ substring(start index, end index)
            // but in java substring(start index, length)
            // For example, if start = 0 and end = 1
            // this means s.substring will take only 1 character
            // starting from 0
            String cur = s.substring(start, end);
            if(dict.contains(cur)) {
                localMin = Math.min(localMin, recurse(end, s, dict));
            }
            else {
                // length of the string we weren't able to take is end - start
                // We haven't considered character of <index end> that's why we recurse from index end.
                localMin = Math.min(localMin, end-start + recurse(end, s, dict));
            }
        }
        return localMin;
    }
}
```

# [Accepted] HashSet + Recursion + Memoization:

We can easily memoize the above solution to avoid unnecessary calculations.

``` java []
class Solution {
