## What if we use some other datastructure instead of HashSet?

# [Accepted] Using Trie: (Beats 98%)

Trie (we pronounce "try") or prefix tree is a tree data structure, which is used for retrieval of a key in a dataset of strings. There are various applications of this very efficient data structure such as :
- Auto Completion
- Genome Sequencing in Bioinformatics
- Spell Checker
- IP Routing (Longest Prefix Matching)

``` java []
class Solution {
    int n;
    TrieNode root;

    public int minExtraChar(String s, String[] dictionary) {
        n = s.length();
        int[] memo = new int[n];
        Arrays.fill(memo, -1);
        buildTrie(dictionary);
        return recurse(0, s, memo);
    }

    int recurse(int start, String s, int[] memo) {
        if(start == n) {
            return 0;
        }
        if(memo[start]!=-1) {
            return memo[start];
        }
        TrieNode node = root;
        // To count this character as a left over character 
        // move to index 'start + 1'
        int localMin = recurse(start+1, s, memo) + 1;

        for(int i=start; i<n; i++) {
            char ch = s.charAt(i);
            if(!node.containsChild(ch)) {
                break;
            }
            node = node.getChild(ch);
            if(node.isWord) {
                localMin = Math.min(localMin, recurse(i+1, s, memo));
            }
        }
        return memo[start] = localMin;
    }

    void buildTrie(String[] words) {
        root = new TrieNode();
        for(String word : words) {
            insert(word);
        }
    }

    public void insert(String word) {
        TrieNode node = root;
        for(char c: word.toCharArray()) {
            if(!node.containsChild(c))
                node.addChild(c);

            node = node.getChild(c);
        }
        node.isWord = true;
    }
}
class TrieNode {
    Map<Character, TrieNode> children;
    boolean isWord;

    public TrieNode() {
        this.children = new HashMap<>();
        this.isWord = false;
    }

    public boolean containsChild(char c) {
        return children.containsKey(c);
    }

    public TrieNode getChild(char c) {
        return children.get(c);
    }

    public void addChild(char c) {
        TrieNode node = new TrieNode();
        this.children.put(c, node);
    }
}
```
