DP:
Let `dp[i]: minimum number of extra character in s[0:i]`,
and we have
```
dp[i] = dp[j - 1], if s[i, j] is in the dictionary
dp[i] = dp[j - 1] + i - j + 1, otherwise
```

```
class Solution {
    public int minExtraChar(String s, String[] dictionary) {
        int n = s.length();
        Set<String> words = new HashSet<>(Arrays.asList(dictionary));
        int[] dp = new int[n + 1];
        Arrays.fill(dp, n + 1);
        dp[0] = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
                String str = s.substring(j, i);
                if (words.contains(str)) {
