# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
* First come up with the solution using hashmap.
* Dp[i] means min number of extra char left in s[i]~s[n-1].
* Try all prefix start at i and check if the substring is in the dictionary. If yes then update dp[i].
* Also we need to consider to left char s[i].

```
class Solution {
public:
    int minExtraChar(string s, vector<string>& dictionary) {
        int n = s.size();
        unordered_set<string> dic;
        for(auto& word : dictionary) {
            dic.insert(word);
        }

        vector<int> dp(n+1, 0);
        for(int i=n-1; i>=0; i--) {
            dp[i] = 1 + dp[i+1];
            for(int j=i; j<n; j++) {
                if(dic.count(s.substr(i, j-i+1))) {
                    dp[i] = min(dp[i], dp[j+1]);
                }
            }
        }
        return dp[0];
    }
};
```
However using hashmap to check the substring need O(L) time. L is the length of the substring. Worst case will be O(n).

- Time complexity: $$O(N^3 + M*L)$$

Using Trie to reduce the searching time to O(1) and break out of the loop when there is no matching prefix to reduce the time.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minExtraChar(string s, vector<string>& dictionary) {
        int n = s.size();
        Node* root = new Node();

        //create Trie
        for(auto& word : dictionary) {
            Node* now = root;
            for(char& c : word) {
                if(!now->child.count(c)) {
                    now->child[c] = new Node();
                }
                now = now->child[c];
            }
            now->is_end = true;
        }

        //dp[i] means min number of extra char left in s[i]~s[n-1]
        vector<int> dp(n+1, 0);
        for(int i=n-1; i>=0; i--) {
            // left s[j]
            dp[i] = 1 + dp[i+1];
            Node* now = root;
            // check if the prefix is in dictionary
            for(int j=i; j<n; j++) {
                // if the prefix is not exist break out of the loop
                // this place can be faster than using hash map
                if(!now->child.count(s[j])) {
                    break;
                }
                now = now->child[s[j]];
                // if the prefix is in dictionary, update dp[i]
                if(now->is_end) {
                    dp[i] = min(dp[i], dp[j+1]);
                }
            }
        }
        return dp[0];
    }
