# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We have to divide the given string into substrings in such a way that we have to minimize the sum of length of substrings which are not present in dictionary.

*In simpler words, we have to divide a string into substrings such that the sum of length of the substrings which are not present in dictionary is minimized.*

Eg:- `s = "leetscode", dictionary = ["leet","code","leetcode"]`
we can divide it into 3 substrings `leet | s | code`
`leet and code belongs to the dictionary, but s doesnot.`
So we have to partition the substring and minimize the sum of `length of substrings` which are not in the dictionary.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- We first insert all dictionary strings to map to check if the string exists in`OLog(N)`.
- We can simply perform a recursion `helper(s, mp, ind)`
Here `ind` refers to the start of our substring. To partition a string we can start a forloop `for(int i = ind; i < s.length(); i++)` indicating that the substring starts from index `ind` and ends at index `i`.
- Now we check if the substring from `ind to ith index` is a part of dictionary.
    - If the substring is a part of dictionary then the number of characters that would be left behind would be `0 + helper(s, mp, i + 1)` i.e 0 + minimum no of characters left behind if substrings start from `i + 1` index (`helper(s, mp, i + 1)`).
    - If the substring is `not` a part of dictionary then the number of characters that would be left behind would be `(i - ind + 1) + helper(s, mp, i + 1)` i.e length of this substring (`(i - ind + 1)`) + minimum no of characters left behind if substrings start from `i + 1` index (` helper(s, mp, i + 1)`).
- We then store the minimum of each partitions into ans.
``` C++ []
//t refers to substring ind to i.
string t = "";
for(int i = ind;i < s.length(); i++){
    t.push_back(s[i]);
    if(mp[t] > 0){
        // substring exists in dictionary.
        ans = min(ans, 0 + helper(s, mp, i + 1));
    }else{
        // substring doesnot exists in dictionary.
        ans = min(ans, (i - ind + 1) + helper(s, mp, i + 1));
    }
}
```


# Complexity
- Time complexity: `O(N) * (max(len(s)))`
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: `O(N) for dictionary`
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```Python []
def helper(s, mp, ind, dp):
    if ind == len(s):
        return 0
    if dp[ind] != -1:
        return dp[ind]
    ans = 1e9
    t = ""
    for i in range(ind, len(s)):
        t += s[i]
        if(t in mp):
            ans = min(ans, helper(s, mp, i + 1, dp))
        else:
            ans = min(ans, i - ind + 1 + helper(s, mp, i + 1, dp))
    dp[ind] = ans
    return dp[ind]

class Solution(object):
    def minExtraChar(self, s, dictionary):
        mp = set()
        dp = [-1] * 51
        for i in dictionary:
            mp.add(i)
        return helper(s, mp, 0, dp)

