# Approach
The problem can be solved using **Dynamic Programming** with following recurrence:
```
    dp[i] = minimum characters left for string[0...i]
    dp[i] = dp[i-1] + 1 (base case, if no match is found)
    dp[i] = min(dp[i], dp[i - len(s[i..j])]), if the substring is in dictionary
```

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O($n^2m$), where m is length of dictionary and n is length of s.

- Space complexity: O($n$)

# Code
```
class Solution { 

    public int minExtraChar(String s, String[] dictionary) {
        int n = s.length();
        int[] dp = new int[n + 1];

        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            dp[i] = dp[i - 1] + 1;

            for (String word : dictionary) {
                int len = word.length();
                if (i >= len && s.substring(i - len, i).equals(word)) {
                    dp[i] = Math.min(dp[i], dp[i - len]);
                }
            }
        }

        return dp[n];
    }
}
```

