# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Check two cases:
1. Skipping current character and count it as missing.
2. Iterate over the all substrings starting with character at i and look for dictionary words.

Optimizing:
3. We can use prefix searching in trie to check whether to continue the loop or not.
This optimization improves runtime from 44%to 94.5%.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
