1) If the sub-string exists,till now no words were extra.
2) If the sub-string does not exist,all the chars in string were extra .So ,extra words would be equal to length of substring.
If substring has i chars, length = i+1
[String is index based 0 , so if substring is of length i , i+1 chars would be extra/useless]

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Iterate over string's length, initially pass given string in the question.
Form substring by concatenating the chars of string and check if the formed substring is present in dictionary.
1) If yes, none of the chars till substring length were extra.so call the method recursively and pass string from i+1 index, so that next time for loop runs from i+1 to s.length()
2) If no, then it means substring formed till now is waste as it is not present in the dictionary .[It might be possible that adding more chars to this substring may get us a word in dictionary--**CASE3**]
so , for now i+1 chars were extra and we call function recursively for i+1 index.

Since, we need to find min chars , we maintain a variable x and asign it to a large value and compare our recursive calls result with it and finally assign the min result to x itself.
This way , we will be able to handle **CASE-3** and also we will get min answer .

Use Dp to memoize our recursive call [cache the result of  recursive calls that are already computed].

Convert input array to Map /Set so that we can check if formed substring is present in our dictionary or not. 


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n^2)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
     Map<String,Integer> diction = new HashMap<>();
    Map<String,Integer> dp = new HashMap<>();
    public int solve(String s){
        if(s.length() == 0){
            return 0;
        }
        if(dp.containsKey(s)){
            return dp.get(s);
        }
        String temp = "";
        int x = 10000;
        for(int i=0 ; i<s.length() ; i++){
            temp += s.charAt(i);
            if(diction.containsKey(temp))
            x = Math.min(x,solve(s.substring(i+1)));
            else
            x = Math.min(x,((i+1) + solve(s.substring(i+1))));
        }
        dp.put(s,x);
        return x;
    }


    public int minExtraChar(String s, String[] dictionary) {

        for(int i=0 ; i<dictionary.length ; i++){
            diction.put(dictionary[i],1);
        }
        return solve(s);
    }

}
